Package: mulberry
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Email and calendar client with IMAP, CalDAV, and CardDAV support
 Mulberry is a traditional desktop email client supporting modern internet
 protocols for email, calendars, and contacts:
 .
  * Email: IMAP4rev1, POP3, SMTP with SSL/TLS encryption
  * Calendars: CalDAV with iCalendar (RFC 5545) format
  * Contacts: CardDAV and LDAP directory services
  * Server-side filtering: SIEVE scripting language
  * Security: GPG and S/MIME encryption support
 .
 Mulberry provides a three-pane interface with offline synchronization,
 message threading, and standards-compliant MIME support. Originally
 developed by Cyrus Daboo and released under the Apache License 2.0,
 this package represents continued community maintenance with modern
 compiler and SSL library support.
 .
 Note: Upstream development appears to be very limited. Users seeking
 actively maintained alternatives should consider Thunderbird or
 Evolution.
